Recent news indicates a surge in small-business and consumer confidence, near record low unemployment claims, and expectations of continued economic momentum. US consumer confidence rose to its highest level since 2000, with consumers feeling more positive about the current economy and their future outlook. Small-business confidence has also reached a record high in 2018, attributed to optimism surrounding the recently enacted tax-reform package. A record number of small-business owners believe it is a good time to expand. Additionally, jobless claims in the US are near a 45-year low, indicating strong job growth and economic momentum. The Federal Reserve views the economy as gaining momentum, partly due to tax cuts and global growth. Overall, there is widespread optimism among small businesses and consumers regarding the US economy.